sendgmail
=========

A simple email sender program using gmail smtp written in Go language.


Usage
=====

First, you should set a gmail account that SMTP is enabled.  Then, write down a
file, `gmailinfo`.  `gmailinfo` file should have account name and password of
your gmail account, recipients, cc, bcc, subject, and message which you are
willing to send.  The file should be written in jason format.  For example,

```
$ cat gmailinfo
{
	"Username":"sendgmail",
	"Password":"sendgmailpassword"
	"Recipients":"foo@bar.com",
	"Cc":"somebody@somewhere.com",
	"Bcc":"",
	"Subject":"Test for sengmail with CC and BCC",
	"Message":"Hello, this is test"
}
```

The path to the file can be changed by using command line options described
below.


Options
-------

There are two command line options.

  -account string
        File that containing information about the mail to send. (default "gmailinfo")
  -dryrun
        Do not send mail, just show what will happen


